eatment under Ernakulam will be discharged today. Therefore, as of now there are 126 positives under treatment.<ref name=\"dhs26\">{{cite news |title=Daily Bulletin|url=http://dhs.kerala.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/bulm_26032020e.pdf|accessdate=26 March 2020 |work=Directorate of Health Services,Kerala |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''27 March''' ||\n* '''39 Cases''' : [[Kollam]] reported its first case along with 34 in [[Kasargod]], 2 in [[Kannur]], 1 each in [[Thrissur]] and [[Kozhikode]].<ref name=\"mbi27\">{{cite news |title=\u0d0e\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32\u0d3e \u0d1c\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32\u0d15\u0d33\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d15\u0d4a\u0d31\u0d4b\u0d23; \u0d07\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d \u0d38\u0d4d\u0d25\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d40\u0d15\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a\u0d24\u0d4d 39\u0d2a\u0d47\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d|url=https://www.mathrubhumi.com/news/kerala/corona-tested-positive-1.4648102|accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=Mathrubhumi|language=en}}</ref> This became the most number of positive cases reported in [[Kerala]] on a single day till now.<ref name=\"dhs27\">{{cite news |title=Daily Bulletin|url=http://dhs.kerala.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Daily-Bulletin-English-27th-March-2.pdf|accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=Directorate of Health Services,Kerala |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''28 March''' ||\n* '''6 Cases''', '''1 Death''' : A 69-year-old male from Pallikkal Bazar, [[Mattancherry]], [[Ernakulam]] who had a travel history from the [[Middle East]] reported to be the first death in [[Kerala]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businesstoday.in/latest/trends/coronavirus-india-cases-deaths-live-updates-lockdown-delhi-mumbai-america-italy-covid19-virus/story/399465.html|title=Coronavirus in India Live Updates: Kerala's first COVID-19 death; positive cases surge to 873|work=businesstoday.in|date=28 March 2020}}</ref> New cases are 2 from [[Thiruvananthapuram]], 1 each in [[Kasargod]], [[Malappuram]], [[Palakkad]] and [[Kollam]].<ref name=\"dhs28\">{{cite news |title=Daily Bulletin|url=http://dhs.kerala.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Daily-Bulletin-HFWD-English-28th-March.pdf|accessdate=28 March 2020 |work=Directorate of Health Services,Kerala |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''29 March'''||\n* '''20 Cases''' : 8 in [[Ernakulam|Kannur]][[Ernakulam|,]] 7 in and [[Kasaragod district|Kasaragod,]] 1 each in  [[Idukki|Thiruvananthapuram]][[Idukki|,]] [[Ernakulam]], [[Thrissur]], [[Kozhikode|Palakkad]] and  [[Malappuram]].Out of 20, 18 active cases has a travel history from [[Dubai]] and rest being person-to-person transmission.4 patients were discharged at [[Pathanamthitta]].<ref name = \"mbi29\">{{cite news |title=\u0d38\u0d02\u0d38\u0d4d\u0d25\u0d3e\u0d28\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4d 20 \u0d2a\u0d47\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d41 \u0d15\u0d42\u0d1f\u0d3f \u0d15\u0d4a\u0d31\u0d4b\u0d23 \u0d38\u0d4d\u0d25\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d40\u0d15\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d1a\u0d4d\u0d1a\u0d41, \u0d0e\u0d31\u0d23\u0d3e\u0d15\u0d41\u0d33\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4d \u0d06\u0d30\u0d4b\u0d17\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d35\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d15\u0d28\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d30\u0d4b\u0d17\u0d02|url=https://www.mathrubhumi.com/news/kerala/20-more-people-tested-positive-with-corona-in-kerala-1.4652612|accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=Mathrubhumi |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"dhs29\">{{cite news |title=Daily Bulletin|url=http://dhs.kerala.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Daily-Bulletin-English-29th-March.pdf|accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=Directorate of Health Services,Kerala |language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''30 March'''||\n* '''32 Cases''' : 15 in [[Kasaragod district|Kasaragod,]] 11 in [[Kannur]], 2 each in  [[Idukki]] and [[Wayanad]].Out of 32, 17 active cases has a travel history  and rest being person-to-person transmission.<ref name = \"mbi30\">{{cite news |title=\u0d38\u0d02\u0d38\u0d4d\u0d25\u0d3e\u0d28\u0d24\u0d