okyo.\n* {{Cite book| author=Smil, V.| title=Enriching the Earth: Fritz Haber, Carl Bosch, and the Transformation of World Food | publisher=MIT Press | year=2001 | id= | isbn=978-0-262-19449-5 |ref=harv}}\n* {{Cite journal|last1=Wheeler |first1=S. A. |year=2008 |title= What influences agricultural professionals' views towards organic agriculture? |journal = Ecological Economics | volume= 65 |pages=145\u2013154 | doi = 10.1016/j.ecolecon.2007.05.014}}\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Wickramasinghe | first1 = L. P. | display-authors = etal | year = 2003 | title = Bat activity and species richness on organic and conventional farms: impact of agricultural intensification | url = http://gcprovence.org/OrganicFarmBats.pdf | journal = Journal of Applied Ecology | volume = 40 | issue = 6 | pages = 984\u201393 | doi = 10.1111/j.1365-2664.2003.00856.x | access-date = 5 November 2013 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20131105082934/http://gcprovence.org/OrganicFarmBats.pdf | archive-date = 5 November 2013 | url-status = dead }}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Prone to spam|date=October 2012}}\n{{Z148}}<!-- {{No more links}}\n\n       Please be cautious adding more external links.\n\nWikipedia is not a collection of links and should not be used for advertising.\n\n     Excessive or inappropriate links will be removed.\n\n See [[Wikipedia:External links]] and [[Wikipedia:Spam]] for details.\n\nIf there are already suitable links, propose additions or replacements on\nthe article's talk page, or submit your link to the relevant category at\nthe Open Directory Project (dmoz.org) and link there using {{Dmoz}}.\n\n -->\n{{Commons|Organic farming|Organic farming}}\n\n* {{dmoz|Science/Agriculture/Sustainable_Agriculture/|Organic Farming}}\n* [http://www.orgprints.org/ Organic Eprints.] A database of research in organic food and farming.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090429042221/http://www.extension.org/organic%20production Organic Agriculture.] eOrganic Community of Practice wit